  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid Intervention and response to provide hemodialysis sessions in Aleppo Governorate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As Aleppo is witnessing an active returning movement in the new accessible areas, and as observed during the field visits which are regularly conducted by WHO Aleppo hub&#x2019;s team to different health partners (MoH facilities, General assemblies, MoHE Hospitals, SARC and NGOs) that provide secondary care services, a critical need for haemodialysis sessions have clearly manifested itself recently.

 WHO office in Aleppo has received several requests from: 1) SARC 2) MoHE and 3) the general assembly of kidney surgical hospital (MoH) for urgent  support with sessions.

With this intervention, WHO aims to fill the gap, strengthen the kidney dialysis services and alleviate the suffering of the patients by the immediate procurement of  10&#x2019;000 sessions for adult which can partially cover the needs of  1250 beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
